---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Projects - Bradley Spillert">
  <section class="pt-32 pb-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="section-heading fade-in">Projects</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-400 mb-12 max-w-2xl fade-in">
        A mix of things I've built for fun, for learning, and because I wanted them to exist. Images and videos coming soon for most of these.
      </p>

      <!-- Featured project -->
      <div class="fade-in group mb-10 bg-surface-raised border border-accent/20 rounded-xl overflow-hidden hover:border-accent/40 transition-all">
        <div class="placeholder-image h-56 md:h-64">
          <span>Image coming soon</span>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 md:p-8">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-white text-xl font-semibold group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">
              <a href="https://github.com/spillertb/flight-software" target="_blank" rel="noopener">flight-software</a>
            </h3>
            <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-accent/15 border border-accent/30 rounded text-[10px] text-accent uppercase tracking-wider">Featured</span>
            <a href="https://github.com/spillertb/flight-software" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-500 hover:text-accent transition-colors ml-auto shrink-0">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="1.5" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>
          <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
            Open source ground control station for <a href="https://ardupilot.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-300 hover:underline">ArduPilot</a> drones. A modern, web-based GCS built with React, TypeScript, and <a href="https://cesium.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-300 hover:underline">CesiumJS</a>. Packaged with Electron for desktop use. This is the main thing I'm working on right now.
          </p>
          <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-4">
            {['React', 'TypeScript', 'CesiumJS', 'Electron', 'ArduPilot'].map((tag) => (
              <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-surface border border-gray-800 rounded text-xs text-gray-500">{tag}</span>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Other projects - staggered grid -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="fade-in group bg-surface-raised border border-gray-800 rounded-xl overflow-hidden hover:border-gray-700 transition-all">
          <div class="placeholder-image h-44">
            <span>Image coming soon</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">Autonomous Quadcopter</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
              7-inch quad running <a href="https://ardupilot.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-300 hover:underline">ArduPilot</a> with <a href="https://www.expresslrs.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-300 hover:underline">ELRS</a> radio. Flies fully autonomous waypoint missions — 5+ miles, no manual input. Built the airframe, tuned the PIDs, set up the telemetry link.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-4">
              {['ArduPilot', 'ELRS', 'FPV', 'Autonomous Flight'].map((tag) => (
                <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-surface border border-gray-800 rounded text-xs text-gray-500">{tag}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="fade-in group bg-surface-raised border border-gray-800 rounded-xl overflow-hidden hover:border-gray-700 transition-all md:mt-8">
          <div class="placeholder-image h-36">
            <span>Image coming soon</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">MAVLink over ELRS</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
              Technical writeup on running MAVLink telemetry over <a href="https://www.expresslrs.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-300 hover:underline">ExpressLRS</a>. How to get reliable bidirectional telemetry on an RC link that was never really designed for it.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-4">
              {['MAVLink', 'ExpressLRS', 'Telemetry', 'Technical Writing'].map((tag) => (
                <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-surface border border-gray-800 rounded text-xs text-gray-500">{tag}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="fade-in group bg-surface-raised border border-gray-800 rounded-xl overflow-hidden hover:border-gray-700 transition-all">
          <div class="placeholder-image h-40">
            <span>Image coming soon</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">CoreXY 3D Printer</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
              Custom FDM 3D printer built from scratch. Designed the frame and motion system in <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/products/fusion-360" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-300 hover:underline">Fusion 360</a>, runs <a href="https://marlinfw.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-300 hover:underline">Marlin</a> firmware. Prints PLA, PETG, and TPU.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-4">
              {['Fusion 360', 'Marlin', '3D Printing', 'Mechanical Design'].map((tag) => (
                <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-surface border border-gray-800 rounded text-xs text-gray-500">{tag}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="fade-in group bg-surface-raised border border-gray-800 rounded-xl overflow-hidden hover:border-gray-700 transition-all md:mt-4">
          <div class="placeholder-image h-48">
            <span>Image coming soon</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-6">
            <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">Gyro Glove</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
              Senior capstone project — a wearable gesture controller for RC aircraft. Tilt your hand, fly the plane. Custom PCBs with IMU, radio transceiver, and a whole lot of signal processing.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-4">
              {['PCB Design', 'IMU', 'Embedded C', 'Wireless'].map((tag) => (
                <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-surface border border-gray-800 rounded text-xs text-gray-500">{tag}</span>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="fade-in group bg-surface-raised border border-gray-800 rounded-xl overflow-hidden hover:border-gray-700 transition-all md:col-span-2">
          <div class="md:flex">
            <div class="placeholder-image h-44 md:h-auto md:w-72 shrink-0">
              <span>Image coming soon</span>
            </div>
            <div class="p-6">
              <h3 class="text-white text-lg font-semibold group-hover:text-accent transition-colors">HackUMass VIII — Best Hardware Hack</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mt-3">
                Won Best Hardware Hack at <a href="https://hackumass.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-300 hover:underline">HackUMass</a> VIII with a 2-motor polar plotter. Draws anything you throw at it using polar coordinates and a couple of steppers. Built in 36 hours on too much coffee.
              </p>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-4">
                {['Hackathon', 'Stepper Motors', 'Arduino', 'Mechanical Design'].map((tag) => (
                  <span class="px-2.5 py-1 bg-surface border border-gray-800 rounded text-xs text-gray-500">{tag}</span>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
